Dirco today confirmed that there were three South African citizens involved in the balloon accident in Egypt. Apart from the deceased, a 34-year-old man, two others, both women were injured and are in a stable condition. The balloon was carrying 16 persons from different countries, including South Africa, Argentina, Australia, France The balloon was carrying 16 persons from different countries, including South Africa, Argentina, Australia, France and Brazil, Dirco said in a statement. ANN7 reporter